works.description: The Chilean-born designer, Sebastian Errazuriz, is known for his uncanny design and art pieces, including the teddy bear coat and a zipper dress. The New York-based artist and designer had a very strong artistic background, which has metamorphosed in his latest piece of functional artworks, aptly titled “Metamorphosis.” The inspiration for the bookshelf came from his grandmother’s ivy-covered garden, and the bookshelf similarly runs along the wall to serve as shelves.
